'''Johan Neerman''' (born May 24, 1959, in Kortrijk, Belgium) is a Belgium architect<ref>Febvre, Jacqueline; Isabelle Monier (September 2001). I.D.P.O.-Neerman Consulting. Paris: A.P.C.I. pp. 104-105. ISBN 2 86227 256 6.</ref>, designer<ref>Sap, Hubert (October 1998). "Johan Neerman". Interieur 98 402: 64.</ref>, inventor and system thinker<ref>
De Smedt, Klara (April 1999). "3 vasies op tentoonstellingsdesign". Kwintessens 56, p. 15.</ref>.
After completing architectural studies<ref>
Osteaux, Francoise (2003). "The global method". Arte news 121: 113.</ref>, Neerman entered Wharton School of University of Pennsylvania. Johan Neerman set up a career as designer of [[transport systems]] and inventor. He holds several [[patents]] in the field of [[transportation design]]<ref>
Janssen, Karel (May 1996). "De stad hertekend". Trends 146: 60.</ref>

